@rhatdan with the following changes:
```diff
-payload='{"Mounts":[{"Type":"volume","source":"test1","Destination":"/mnt/scratch","options":"rw"}]}'
-t POST libpod/containers/create Image=$IMAGE Data="$payload" 201 .Id~[0-9a-f]\\{64\\}
+payload='{"Mounts":[{"Type":"volume","source":"test1","Target":"/mnt/scratchme","options":["rw"]}]}'
+t POST containers/create Image=$IMAGE HostConfig="$payload" 201 .Id~[0-9a-f]\\{64\\}
```
(remove `libpod`; change `Destination` to `Target`; and change `Data` to `HostConfig`), `/mnt/scratch` starts appearing in `.HostConfig.Mounts`, although it looks like a list not an indexable object. Those obviously test a different endpoint, so I don't know if it helps you in any way, but that's as much as I can do to help.
